            <div hand="Smyth,Ethel"> <!-- Hand, die den Brief geschrieben hat -->
                <opener>
                    <adress></adress>
                    <note><before rend="underline"></before> Xmas 77<unclear quantity="1" unit="word"></unclear><add place="top"></add></note> <!-- Mit Bleistift  -->
                    <date>Saturday.</date>
                    <salute> My own darling <persName>Mother</persName></salute>
                    ## siehe https://tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-opener.html
                </opener>
                <p> <!-- paragraph ohne Nummerierung, wenn Nummerierung dann p n=x -->
                    <pb/>I have written in 
                    <lb></lb>all 12 Xmas letters! (<unclear quantity="1" unit="word"></unclear> home people!)
                    <lb></lb> & now as a bonne bouche write my letter 
                    <lb></lb>to you. Mother darling I wish you knew how 
                    <lb></lb>much I am thinking of you all – I don’t 
                    <lb></lb><choice><sic cert="high">think </sic></choice> you’ve been out of my thoughts 
                    <lb></lb>one hour ever since the Xmas season came 
                    <lb></lb>in - & as the Xmas day draws near I feel 
                    <lb></lb>more & more the many miles there are 
                    <lb></lb>between us – A very very happy Xmas 
                    <lb></lb>to you Mother darling and a bright New 
                    <lb></lb>Year – Your dear note <choice><sic cert="medium">announced</sic></choice> the 
                    <lb></lb><del rend="overstrike">arrival</del><add place="above">dispatch</add> of the box <hi rend="underline">just</hi> arrived. I 
                    <lb></lb>will lett <persName cert="low">Frau B.</persName> that you <choice><abbr>w</abbr><expan>will</expan></choice> ? Earlier I 
                    <lb></lb>did not go décolletée and I’m sure 
                    <lb></lb>there‘ll be no difficulty about it. 
                    <lb></lb>The beautiful white dress will do 
                    <lb></lb>for <persName>Baroness Tauchnitz</persName> grand party on 
                    <lb></lb>the <date>14th</date>. It sounds much too good 
                    <lb></lb>for a ball & certainly shall not be worn 
                    <lb></lb>at one. And now I must for <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"></unclear>
                    <lb></lb>plunge into what I think will please 
                    <lb></lb>Papa immensely. Some time ago I found 
                    <lb></lb>out that a good many <unclear cert="high">Conservatorists</unclear>
                    <lb></lb>who have <hi rend="underline">excellent</hi> food & a room 
                    <lb></lb>five times the size of mine – also <hi rend="underline">not</hi> 
                    <lb></lb><unclear quantity="1" ></unclear> 3 <unclear quantity="2" cert="medium">pair upstairs</unclear>are paying <num>28</num> 
                    
                    <pb/>
                    <lb></lb>Thaler a month – <choice><abbr>i.e.</abbr><expan>that is to say</expan></choice> <choice><abbr>₤</abbr><expan>Pound</expan></choice> <num>4.2</num> a month
                    <lb></lb>– <num>50.4.0</num> per annum – whereas I 
                    <lb></lb>pay as you know <num>40</num> Thalers – <choice><abbr>i.e.</abbr><expan>that is to say</expan></choice> 
                    <lb></lb></choice> <choice><abbr>₤</abbr><expan>Pound</expan></choice> <num>6</num> a month (rather more as a fact) 
                    <lb></lb>& </choice> <choice><abbr>₤</abbr><expan>Pound</expan></choice> <num>75</num> a year!! I didn’t <unclear cert="medium">wate</unclear> about 
                    <lb></lb>it at once as I thought the quarter
                    <lb></lb>having been paid on advance I’d better 
                    <lb></lb>make all enquiries first at all 
                    <lb></lb>events secure <del rend="overstrike">two</del><add place="above"><num>3</num></add> points – that 
                    <lb></lb><persName>Mr Burnaud</persName> leaves in <date cert="low">Feb 3</date> – not that 
                    <lb></lb>I get the <persName>Frau Prof’s</persName> drawing room 
                    <lb></lb>a very decent room – yet dear at 
                    <lb></lb>the price – that she promises & 
                    <lb></lb>have no more gentlemen un <unclear cert="low">peu-</unclear>
                    <lb></lb><unclear cert="low">loin</unclear> – as here it is <hi rend="underline">not</hi> <hi rend="underline">conveneable</hi>.
                    <lb></lb>Well – <persName>Mr. Burnaud</persName> is <del rend="overstrike">also</del> <unclear quantity="1"><unit>word</unit></unclear>
                    <lb></lb>-who like us – knew nothing of <unclear cert="medium">her</unclear> –
                    <lb></lb>man rater – pays also <choice><abbr>₤</abbr><expan>Pound</expan></choice> <num>75</num> a year
                    <lb></lb>& grunbles not thereat – If I de-
                    <lb></lb>parted in Feb-3 <persName>Mr. B</persName> <choice><abbr>w°</abbr><expan>would</expan></choice> stay on 
                    <lb></lb>half a year for certain – so all things
                    <lb></lb>considered the <persName>Frau Prof</persName> – who <unclear cert="low"><unit>word</unit></unclear>
                    <lb></lb>a dear old thing so but human &
                    <lb></lb>naturally wishes to get as much from
                    <lb></lb>people as she can (small blame to her)
                    <lb></lb><persName>Frau Prof</persName>considered it a better
                    <lb></lb> <unclear quantity="1"><unit>word</unit></unclear>to keep him – so with
                    
                    <pb/>
                    <lb></lb><hi rend="underline">real</hi> regrets on both sides we decided
                    <lb></lb>it <choice><abbr>w'</abbr><expan>will</expan></choice> be better that I leave on the <date>1st</date>.
                    <lb></lb>I happened to mention to my piano
                    <lb></lb>master that I was leaving (all
                    <lb></lb>happened yesterday) & he instantly 
                    <lb></lb>recommended a mother that he knows
                    <lb></lb>very well – I said <quote>„is it very <unclear quantity="1"><unit>word</unit></unclear>“</quote>
                    <lb></lb><quote>„The usual thing“</quote> he said <quote>“20 Thaler!!”</quote>
                    <lb></lb><quote>“a month!!!”</quote> – He said my paying 
                    <lb></lb><num>40</num> for my room <unclear cert="low">dere</unclear> was a <hi rend="underline">fearful</hi>
                    <lb></lb>swindle!! I instantly went to the 
                    <lb></lb>pension – It is in the nicest part 
                    <lb></lb>of <placeName>Leipzig</placeName> – part oft he big <placeName>Augustus
                        <lb></lb>Platz</placeName> – <num>2</num> houses from a <unclear quantity="1"><unit>word</unit></unclear> of
                    <lb></lb><persName>Frau Brockhaus</persName> - & <num>2</num> streets from 
                    <lb></lb><persName cert="low">Frau B Lenself</persName>!. I liked the <unclear cert="medium">Frau</unclear> &
                    <lb></lb>her wife <hi rend="underline">tremendously</hi> & also the 
                    <lb></lb>room I <choice><abbr>sh°</abbr><expan>shall</expan></choice> – They have no 
                    <lb></lb>gentlemen pensionated & no musical
                    <lb></lb>pensionats – <persName>Frau Brockhaus</persName> will
                    <lb></lb>come with me & look at it all next
                    <lb></lb>week & if the <unclear quantity="2"><unit>word</unit></unclear> desirable I’d
                    <lb></lb>better close - You see here I pay
                    <lb></lb><choice><abbr>₤</abbr><expan>Pound</expan></choice> <num>6.5</num> a month. There <choice><abbr>₤</abbr><expan>Pound</expan></choice><num>4.14</num> so 
                    <lb></lb>that will be a difference of <choice><abbr>₤</abbr><expan>Pound</expan></choice> <num>1.11</num>
                    <lb></lb>a month. & for the <num>6</num> months I shall
                    <lb></lb>be here before coming home (as a matter
                    <lb></lb>of fact it will be less of course)
                    
                    <pb/>
                    ...
                    
                    ## siehe https://tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-p.html
                </p>
